The Nedbank Golf Challenge was briefly brought to a standstill by a business of mongooses. CAPE TOWN - The Nedbank Golf Challenge was briefly interrupted after a business of mongooses scurried onto one of the greens at the Gary Player Country Club just as players were about to make their putts.The field invasion by around 20 mongooses was caught on camera. In the clip, the group could be seen heading straight for an in-play ball.The mongooses are thought to have come from the bordering Pilanesberg Game Reserve.WATCH: Pack of mongooses invade the green during game of golf